2003-03-12 Albert Chu <chu11@llnl.gov>
           - moved unnecessary #defines and #includes from nodeupdown.h
	     to nodeupdown.c
	   - updated library to use new genders_testnode() function
	   - added corner case check for NODEUPDOWN_ERR_NULLPTR 
	     possibility, and appropriate error handling for it.
	   - renamed nodeupdown_get_hostlist_alternate_names() and
	             nodeupdown_get_list_alternate_names() into
	             nodeupdown_convert_hostlist_to_altnames() and
	             nodeupdown_convert_list_to_altnames() respectively.
	   - added len parameter to nodeupdown_convert_list_to_altnames()
	   - removed library's dependence on hostlist structures
	     as part of the API interface.  Did so by placing
	     the following in "#ifdef NODEUPDOWN_HOSTLIST_API".
	     - int nodeupdown_get_up_nodes_hostlist();
	     - int nodeupdown_get_down_nodes_hostlist();
	     - int nodeupdown_convert_hostlist_to_altnames();
           - Added the following new functions
	     - nodeupdown_get_up_nodes_string()
	     - nodeupdown_get_down_nodes_string()
	     - nodeupdown_get_up_nodes_string_altnames()
	     - nodeupdown_get_down_nodes_string_altnames()
	     - nodeupdown_get_up_nodes_list_altnames()
	     - nodeupdown_get_down_nodes_list_altnames()
	     - nodeupdown_convert_string_to_altnames()
	   - Added the following functions, but inside 
	     "#ifdef NODEUPDOWN_HOSTLIST_API"
	     - int nodeupdown_get_up_nodes_hostlist_altnames();
	     - int nodeupdown_get_down_nodes_hostlist_altnames();
	   - updated whatsup command for new API
	   - added -V (version) option to whatsup
	   - updated manpages appropriately
	   - tagged whatsup-1-0-3 

